20 WHEREAS, on March 5, 2025, Bonnie Pollock, who has been an educator for
21 twelve (12) years, received a prestigious Milken Educator Award and its
22 accompanying prize of twenty-five thousand dollars ($25,000); and
23
24 WHEREAS, Bonnie Pollock currently teaches grade six (6) at Old High
25 Middle School in Bentonville, Arkansas; and
26
27 WHEREAS, the Milken Educator Award, also known as the "Oscars of
28 Teaching", is always presented in a surprise ceremony for recipients because
29 educators do not apply for the award but instead are confidentially
30 recommended to the Milken Family Foundation by a blue-ribbon panel appointed
31 by each state's department of education; and
32
33 WHEREAS, in addition to the prize of twenty-five thousand dollars
34 ($25,000), recipients of the Milken Educator Award are paired with veteran
35 Milken Educator Award recipients as part of the mentorship program Milken
36 Friends Forever; and
