2 WHEREAS, Bonnie Pollock has been invited to attend the annual Milken
3 Educator Awards Forum in Los Angeles, California, in April 2025; and
4
5 WHEREAS, Bonnie Pollock is known for having a transformative classroom,
6 fostering collaboration, and propelling student growth; and
7
8 WHEREAS, Bonnie Pollock said of her students, "Last year, Arkansas did
9 the first Civics Bee and I had five of the nine finalists at state from my
10 sixth-grade class. I [taught] sixth grade literacy and social studies last
11 year, so that was just a way to connect social studies and writing to a real-
12 world thing"; and
13
14 WHEREAS, Secretary of the Department of Education Jacob Oliva said of
15 Bonnie Pollock's win, "We're talking about the great work that's happening in
16 the State of Arkansas that has been recognized at a national level. For our
17 teachers' names to go across the finish line is saying you're not only just
18 great in the State of Arkansas, but you're one of the greatest teachers in
19 the nation. It's something that we're very proud to be a part of"; and
20
21 WHEREAS, Bonnie Pollock said of her win, "I'm very shocked and
22 overwhelmed . . . [The school administration is] pushing us to change and
23 think in creative ways . . . a lesson may go poorly, but I have the
24 permission and the forgiveness ahead of time to try something new if I think
25 that it's going to work for our kids",
26
27 NOW THEREFORE,
28 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE NINETY-FIFTH GENERAL
29 ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
30
31 THAT the House of Representatives congratulate Bentonville educator
32 Bonnie Pollock for receiving a Milken Educator Award and its accompanying
33 prize of twenty-five thousand dollars ($25,000).
